<CO>
   SLM
</CO>
<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
MORTGAGES, MORTGAGE BANKERS, MORTGAGE-BACKED SECURITIES (MOR)
</IN>
<LP>
   The following is a listing of securities called for
partial or complete redemption during the week ended Aug. 10,
1990. The notices are taken from advertisements appearing in
editions of The Wall Street Journal, and are not meant to be
definitive. Inquiries regarding specific issues should be
directed to the paying agent or, if none is listed, the
issuer.
                                                                                                       

                          MUNICIPALS
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   ADAMS COUNTY, COLO., will call for redemption $250,000 of
single-family mortgage revenue bonds, 1980 series B, due
Sept. 1, 1993, 1995 and 2011, on Sept. 1, 1990. First
Interstate Bank of Denver is trustee.
   BEAVER COUNTY INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY will call
pollution control revenue bonds, 1975 series B, Duquesne
Light Co. Mansfield project, on Oct. 1, 1990; and 1977 series
E, Cleveland Electric Illuminating Co. Mansfield project, due
Sept. 15, 1992, on Sept. 15, 1990. Ameritrust Co., Cleveland,
is trustee.
   BI-STATE DEVELOPMENT AGENCY, MISSOURI-ILLINOIS
METROPOLITAN DISTRICT will call St. Louis Metropolitan Area
Transit revenue bonds, series 1963, due March 1, 1993, on
Sept. 1, 1990. Mercantile Bank of St. Louis is paying agent.
   DADE COUNTY, FLA., HOUSING FINANCE AUTHORITY, on Sept. 1,
1990, will call for redemption $2.5 million principal amount
of its Florida single-family mortgage revenue bonds, Series
1980, due Sept. 9, 1991-1996 and 2011. Chemical Bank, New
York, N.Y., is paying agent.
   FLAT ROCK, MICH., will recall on Sept. 1, 1990, $750,000
of industrial development revenue bonds, Ford Motor Co.,
series A, due Sept. 1, 1992 and $750,000 of series B bonds,
due Sept. 1, 1991. Morgan Guaranty Trust Co., New York, and
Manufacturers Bank of Detroit are paying agents.
   ONEIDA COUNTY, N.Y., will redeem $1.15 million of
industrial development revenue bonds, 1972 series A, Allied
Mills project, due March 1, 1992, on Sept. 4, 1990. Marine
Midland Bank, New York, is trustee.
   PALM BEACH COUNTY, FLA., HOUSING FINANCE AUTHORITY will
recall $80 million of single-family mortgage purchase revenue
bonds, 1980 series, due Sept. 1, 19911994, 2000, 2005, and
2012. Redemption date is Sept. 1, 1990. Barnett Banks of
South Florida, Jacksonville, is trustee.
   PAYNE COUNTY, OKLA., will on Sept. 1, 1990, recall
$1,395,000 of single-family mortgage revenue bonds, 1980
series A, due 1991-1995 and Sept. 1, 2010. Bank of Oklahoma,
Tulsa, and Chase Manhattan Bank, New York, are paying agents.
   PHOENIX MUTUAL MORTGAGE FUNDING CORP. will redeem
$33,561,600 principal amount of its 10 1/4% sinking fund
bonds, due Sept. 12, 1992, on Sept. 12, 1990. The Chase
Manhattan Bank, Luxembourg-Grand; London, England, and
Geneva, Switzerland, and Banque de Commerce, S.A., Brussels,
Belgium, are paying agents.
   SECOND COLUMBUS HOUSING DEVELOPMENT CORP. will recall on
Sept. 1, 1990, $5,000 of 13.33% mortgage revenue bonds due
Sept. 1, 2024, Bull Creek Apartments/ FHA-insured and section
8 assisted project. Shawmut Bank, Boston and Hartford, Conn.,
is paying agent.
   SOMERSET COUNTY, MD., will call $400,000 of economic
development development revenue bonds, Sysco Corp. series
1982, due Sept. 1, 1992, on Sept. 1, 1990. First City, Texas,
Houston, is paying agent.
   SOUTHWESTERN COUNTIES, COLO., will call for redemption
$315,000 of single-family mortgage participation revenue
bonds, series 1979, on Sept. 1, 1990. Bonds mature on Sept.
1, 1991-1999 and 2011. First Interstate Bank of Denver is
trustee.
   SUMMIT COUNTY, OHIO, on Sept. 1, 1990, will recall
$165,000 principal amount of economic development revenue
bonds, series 1982 R&amp;A Properties project, due Sept. 1, 2012.
Bankers Trust Co., New York, is paying agent.
   URBANA, ILL., on Sept. 1, 1990, will redeem $265,000 of
residential mortgage revenue bonds series 1979, due Sept. 1,
1991-1996 and 2006. Continental Bank, Chicago, is paying
agent.
   CORPORATES EUROPEAN INVESTMENT BANK will call for
redemption on Oct. 1, 1990, $2,468,000 principal amount of
its 8 3/8% bonds due Oct. 1, 1992, and $3,623,000 principal
amount of its 9 1/8% bonds due Oct. 1, 1998. Citibank, New
York, N.Y., is paying agent.
   INDIANAPOLIS POWER &amp; LIGHT CO. will call $160,000
principal amount of its 9 7/8% first mortgage bonds, due
Sept. 15, 2005, on Sept. 15, 1990. American National Bank &amp;
Trust Co. of Chicago, Ill., is trustee.
   STUDENT LOAN MARKETING ASSOCIATION will call its 9.25%
notes due Sept. 10, 1992, on Sept. 10, 1990. The Federal
Reserve Bank of New York is paying agent.
</TEXT>
