and $66 million 7.95% term bonds priced at par, due June 1,
2023. In Series 14 there are $31 million 7.70% term bonds
priced at par due Dec. 1, 2014. Series 15 current interest
serial bonds are priced at par to yield from 6.10% in 1991 to
7.50% in 2004 and 2005. Interest on Series 13 and 15 bonds
will be treated as a preference item in calculating the
Federal alternative minimum tax that may be imposed on
certain investors. The bonds are rated double-A by Moody's
and single-A-plus by S&amp;P.
