<HL>
   Business Brief -- Citizens Utilities Co.:
   Net Income for 2nd Quarter
   Reported at $23.3 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
08/15/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CITUA
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Citizens Utilities Co. said it had second quarter net
income of $23.3 million, or 56 cents a share on both its
Series A and Series B stock.
   That was up 13% from a year-earlier $20.6 million, or 45
cents a share on its Series A stock and 46 cents a share on
its Series B stock. The Stamford, Conn.-based company's
common stock is in two series.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Second-quarter revenue increased 9.8% to $88.5 million
from a year-ago $80.6 million.
   The utility holding company said rate increases for its
water and wastewater operations in Arizona and California
increased revenues $1.4 million. The company added that it
has applications pending to increase rates in Colorado,
Pennsylvania and Vermont that could increase revenues by $6
million.
</TEXT>
