<HL>
   Treasury Plans Sale
   Of $18.4 Billion of Bills
</HL>
<DATE>
08/15/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C6
</SO>
<IN>
CDS, INTEREST RATES, COMMERCIAL PAPER (FIN)
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<GV>
TREASURY DEPARTMENT (TRE)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Treasury plans to raise $2.28 billion in
new cash with the sale Monday of about $18.4 billion in
short-term bills to redeem $16.12 billion in maturing bills.
   The offering will be divided evenly between 13-week and
26-week bills maturing on Nov. 23, 1990, and Feb. 21, 1991,
respectively.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Tenders for the bills, available in minimum $10,000
denominations, must be received by 1 p.m. EDT Monday at the
Treasury or at Federal Reserve banks or branches.
