   Business Brief -- Sequa Corp.:
   Earnings for 2nd Quarter
   Rose 8.1%; Units Improve
</HL>
<DATE>
08/15/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   SQAA
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Sequa Corp. said second quarter net earnings rose 8.1%,
reflecting improved earnings at its aerospace and specialty
chemicals units.
   The company's net income for the quarter was $19.7
million, or $1.94 a share, compared to $18.2 million, or
$1.67 a share, during the year-earlier period. Sequa posted
revenue of $568.4 million, up from $482.8 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sequa's results during the second quarter of 1989 included
earnings from discontinued operations of $1.3 million, or 13
cents a share. Per share results for 1990 are based on
approximately 9.6 million shares outstanding; 1989 results
are based on 10.3 million shares outstanding. The company has
been buying back shares since late 1987, including about
300,000 acquired shares in 1990.
   For the six months, New York-based Sequa reported net
income of $38 million, or, $3.72 a share, compared to $38.6
million, or $3.55 a share during 1989. Revenues during the
six months increased to $1.1 billion from $930,000.
