<LP>
   First Executive Corp. reported a 40% drop in
second-quarter earnings and a sharp decline in assets that
may in part reflect substantial numbers of insurance policy
surrenders.
   The Los Angeles-based insurance holding company posted net
income of $30.5 million, or 10 cents a share, down from $51
