   Business Brief -- Health Care Property Investors:
   Real Estate Trust to Buy,
   Lease Back 12 Facilities
</HL>
<DATE>
08/15/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CMDA HCP
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Health Care Property Investors Inc. said it agreed to
acquire 12 medical facilities from Charter Medical Corp. of
Macon, Ga., for $76.2 million, and lease back the facilities
to Charter.
   The transaction is scheduled to be completed by Sept. 30.
In addition, if certain conditions are met, Health Care
Property would acquire and lease back five additional
properties for about $36 million near the end of the first
quarter of next year.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The initial 12 facilities to be acquired include nine
psychiatric hospitals with 652 beds, one acute general
hospital with 103 beds, and two adjoining medical office
buildings. The facilities are located in six states in the
Southeast and Midwest.
   Health Care Property is a real estate investment trust
that invests in health care facilities.
